Class ClientDatabase

java.lang.Object
  commandserver.ClientDatabase

public class ClientDatabase
extends java.lang.Object

The database of ClientRecords. Uses a TreeMap (for now) as the data structure, and ClientRecords as the nodes.

Author:
W. Taff and P. Salevski

setClientStatus

public java.lang.Boolean setClientStatus(java.lang.String hostID,
                                         java.lang.String status)
Allows client to set their status in status box of record. Only clients shall write their status to their status box. Read by the server to ascertain status of the client.

Parameters:
hostID - - uid_host of the host of interest
status - - String of status value of host.
Returns:
True of status written, False if record not found

setClientInbox

public java.lang.Boolean setClientInbox(java.lang.String hostID,
                                        java.lang.String message)
Allows server to write message to client inbox. Only servers shall write to the client inbox. Read by clients to ascertain their instructions from server.

Parameters:
hostID - - uid_host of the host of interest
message - - String of message FROM server TO client.
Returns:
True if inbox message written, False if record not found
